{meta: title You Belong To My Heart}
{meta: artist Marty Robbins}
{meta: writer Ray Gilbert, Aguirre Agustin Lara}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]You belong to my heart
Now and [D7]forever
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
And our love had its start
Not long [G]ago
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
We were gathering stars
While a million guitars played our love [D7]song
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
When I said I love you
Every beat of my heart said it [G]too
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
'Twas a moment like this
Do you [D7]remember
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
And your eyes threw a kiss
When they met [G]mine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Now we own all the stars
And a million guitars are still [D7]playing
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
Darling you are the song
And you'll always belong to my [G]heart
{end_of_verse}
